<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Brooks</ENAMEX> Act, eliminating GSAÂ«s central acquisition <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG_DESC">authority</ENAMEX>.
Primary procurement responsibility now rests directly with federal
<ENAMEX TYPE="ORG_DESC">agencies</ENAMEX>.
Together with a number of other laws enacted over the past
<TIMEX TYPE="DATE">several years</TIMEX> to foster improvements in such areas as financial
<ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">management</ENAMEX>, acquisition, and computer security, this legislation
discussed above composes a statutory framework for achieving
<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">performance-based</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">management</ENAMEX> and accountability in not just
<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">information</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">management</ENAMEX>, but overall federal management<NUMEX TYPE="MONEY">.3</NUMEX> (Appendix
